item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: Admin
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

Lala Deshbandhu Gupta, a patriot who had dedicated his life to the national freedom struggle. It is a separate entity and will have a new campus in 7 acres of land in Kalkaji, New Delhi. The college is very much affiliated to the Delhi University and is purely funded by UGC. Located in one of the posh areas of South Delhi, Ramanujan College offers degree courses in Commerce and Humanities; it being the third largest college for Commerce education in DU. The distinguished and eminent faculty members of the college, apart from being involved in post graduate teaching at the university, have published original and innovative work in journals of national and international repute. We have been highly privileged to be awarded with the ‘Teaching and Learning Centre’ project last year. TLC entails the establishment of a center where University faculty, staff, and community members tie-up and collaborate to enhance the quality of the education. By providing an environment to encourage the involved participators, we aim to improve the teaching pedagogy to promote innovation and interest among the students from diverse backgrounds.

A number of factors have led to the college's desire to establish a Teaching-Learning Centre:
  • The College understands the immense thrust imposed by global issues. To tackle these problems, an all the more competent generation is required. To be able to produce such batches, the education given to them should be qualitative, research oriented and thought provoking.
  • The Indian institutions have not been assessed at a high rank in the global scene, a situation that needs to be analyzed and definitely improved.
  • The student profile is changing. Students from various economical and religious sections of the society are making their presence felt in all renowned institutions. Their needs are different and it is mandatory to address their requirements in a focused manner to truly benefit this strata.
  • The faculty now comprises of the younger population, a case evident in our college. It is important to inculcate in them such practices that are vital to cater to students through the experience of senior faculty members and experts.
  • Though, most faculties are well versed with technology, but still a sustained faculty development effort is needed to deploy the technology for effective teaching. Online learning, e-content and other emerging modes of pedagogy are ways that can drastically improve the medium of communication with students.
  • A comprehensive student and teacher evaluation plan needs to be developed that can remove the pressure on students and assess the all round performance of a student and hence grade them.

  • The College strives to make the learning environment student centric and student friendly both in terms of infrastructure and human resource. There is considerable emphasis on interactive class room teaching.
  • The students are given time and freedom to work on a wide range of projects and assignments.
  • The College is ICT enabled and all classrooms are provided with projectors. The campus is wifi enabled. All teachers have been provided with laptop computers.
  • Power point presentations, demonstration through film clips are extensively used in pedagogic practices helping the student to learn effectively.
  • The library has the latest books and book demands from students are also accommodated.
  • The Department Associations organize festivals, showcasing academic talents through quizzes, essay writing, debates and presentations.
  • Role plays, paper presentations have been inculcated in classroom teaching.
  • Bilingual mode of teaching is used to cater to students from all backgrounds.
